10 (3) Provide a [state treasurer-approved] receipt
11 approved by the department of elementary and secondary
12 education to taxpayers for contributions made to the
13 organization;
14 (4) Ensure that grants are distributed to scholarship
15 accounts of qualified students in the following order:
16 (a) Qualified students who received a scholarship
17 grant in the previous school year;
18 (b) Qualified students who are siblings of qualified
19 students who will receive a scholarship grant in the current
20 school year;
21 (c) Qualified students that have an approved
22 "individualized education plan" (IEP) developed under the
23 federal Individuals with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA),
24 20 U.S.C. Section 1400, et seq., as amended, or who have
25 been diagnosed with dyslexia, as the term "dyslexia" is
26 defined in section 633.420;
27 (d) Qualified students who are eligible for free lunch
28 as approved by the department of elementary and secondary
29 education in accordance with federal regulations and who
7

30 reside in an unaccredited or provisionally accredited school
31 district;
32 (e) Qualified students who are eligible for reduced
33 price lunch as approved by the department of elementary and
34 secondary education in accordance with federal regulations
35 and who reside in an unaccredited or provisionally
36 accredited school district;
37 (f) Qualified students who are eligible for free lunch
38 as approved by the department of elementary and secondary
39 education in accordance with federal regulations;
40 (g) Qualified students who are eligible for reduced
41 price lunch as approved by the department of elementary and
42 secondary education in accordance with federal regulations;
43 (h) Qualified students who are active duty military
44 dependents who have relocated to Missouri and are enrolling
45 in a school in the state for the first time; and
46 (i) All other qualified students;
47 (5) Ensure that:
48 (a) One hundred percent of such organization's
49 revenues from interest or investments is spent on
